## System.LimitException: Too many DML statements: 151

This error occurs when performing a DML operation inside a for loop. Salesforce imposes a limitation of 150 DML operations per transaction, 
and exceeding this limit by even one additional DML operation will result in this error.

# Error Example
public class errorListDemo {
    
    // System.LimitException: Too many DML statements: 151
    public static void governorLimitDMLDemo(){
        for(Integer i=0; i<=151; i++) {
            Account acc = new Account();
            acc.Name = 'Test';
            insert acc;
        }
    }
}

If you use this pattern in your code, you will encounter the error: System.LimitException: Too many DML statements: 151.

To avoid this type of error, you can use the following code pattern.

# Error Solution
public class errorListDemo {
    
    // Avoid System.LimitException: Too many DML statements: 151
    public static void governorLimitDMLDemo() {
        
        List<Account> accountList = new List<Account>();
        for(Integer i = 0; i <= 151; i++) {
            Account acc = new Account();
            acc.Name = 'Test ' + i;
            accountList.add(acc); 
        }
        
        insert accountList;
    }
}
